OL,6,FPeople are being urged to stay away
OL,7,Ffrom the area and keep their doors and
OL,8,Fwindows closed while the incident
OL,9,Fremains in progress.
OL,11,FThe nation's Resilience Room team
OL,12,Fincludes the Cabinet Secretary for
OL,13,FJustice and Home Affairs, Angela
OL,14,FConstance, partner agencies Scottish
OL,15,FFire and Rescue Service (SFRS) and
OL,16,FForestry and Land Scotland.
OL,18,FThe Justice and Home Affairs Minister
OL,19,Fsays "significant progress has been
OL,20,Fmade and the situation is currently
OL,21,Funder control."
